Tu as raison вҖ” mon prГ©cГ©dent schГ©ma ne respectait pas ta double fractale IVCГ—DRO.
Voici la forme canonique minimale conforme, prГӘte Г  copier-coller.
MetaSchema вҖ” IVCГ—DRO (double fractale, symГ©trique)


Orientation primaire: IVC вҶ’ (D,R,O)


Projection miroir: DRO вҶ’ (I,V,C) (vue calculГ©e pour la symГ©trie)


Transversal: lifecycle + vecteur DRO + index croisГ©


jsonCopier le code{
  "META": {
    "name": "MetaSchema_IVCxDRO",
    "version": "0.2"
  },

  "IDENTY": {
    "DEFINITION": { "id": "<uuid>", "name": "<string>", "type": "<string>" },
    "RULE": {
      "required": ["id","name","type"],
      "validators": [],
      "lifecycle_ref": "TRANSVERSAL.LIFECYCLE"
    },
    "OPTION": { "defaults": {}, "hints": [] }
  },

  "VIEW": {
    "DEFINITION": { "status": "draft", "labels": [] },
    "RULE": { "required": ["status"], "validators": [] },
    "OPTION": { "ui": {}, "formats": [] }
  },

  "CONTEXT": {
    "DEFINITION": { "relations": [], "tags": [] },
    "RULE": { "required": [], "validators": [] },
    "OPTION": { "scopes": [], "indices": [] }
  },

  "DRO_PROJECTION": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "IDENTY": { "$ref": "IDENTY.DEFINITION" },
      "VIEW":   { "$ref": "VIEW.DEFINITION" },
      "CONTEXT":{ "$ref": "CONTEXT.DEFINITION" }
    },
    "RULE": {
      "IDENTY": { "$ref": "IDENTY.RULE" },
      "VIEW":   { "$ref": "VIEW.RULE" },
      "CONTEXT":{ "$ref": "CONTEXT.RULE" }
    },
    "OPTION": {
      "IDENTY": { "$ref": "IDENTY.OPTION" },
      "VIEW":   { "$ref": "VIEW.OPTION" },
      "CONTEXT":{ "$ref": "CONTEXT.OPTION" }
    }
  },

  "TRANSVERSAL": {
    "LIFECYCLE": {
      "state": "draft",
      "states": ["draft","defined","built","tested","optimized","rendered","archived"],
      "transitions": {
        "draft->defined": ["define","spec"],
        "defined->built": ["create","build","update"],
        "built->tested": ["test","validate","evaluate"],
        "tested->optimized": ["optimize","refactor","improve"],
        "optimized->rendered": ["render","publish","ship"],
        "rendered->archived": ["archive"]
      },
      "hooks": { "on_enter": {}, "on_exit": {} },
      "timestamps": { "created_at": null, "updated_at": null, "state_changed_at": null }
    },

    "DRO_VECTOR": {
      "DEFINITION": [],   "RULE": [],   "OPTION": []
    },

    "XMAP": {
      "by_path": { "IDENTY.DEFINITION.name": "string" },
      "aliases": {}
    }
  }
}

Exemple de schГ©ma Website (respect strict de la double fractale)
jsonCopier le code{
  "META": { "name": "Website.schema", "version": "0.1", "extends": "MetaSchema_IVCxDRO" },

  "IDENTY": {
    "DEFINITION": { "id": "<uuid>", "name": "<string>", "type": "Website" },
    "RULE": { "required": ["name","type"], "validators": [] },
    "OPTION": { "defaults": {} }
  },

  "VIEW": {
    "DEFINITION": { "status": "draft", "labels": [], "domain": "<string>" },
    "RULE": { "required": ["status","domain"], "validators": [] },
    "OPTION": { "ui": { "icon": "рҹҢҗ" } }
  },

  "CONTEXT": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "relations": [
        { "rel": "has_page", "to_type": "Page", "card": "1..*" },
        { "rel": "owned_by", "to_type": "Company", "card": "1" }
      ],
      "tags": []
    },
    "RULE": { "required": [], "validators": [] },
    "OPTION": { "indices": ["VIEW.DEFINITION.domain"] }
  },

  "DRO_PROJECTION": { "$mirror_of": "IVC" },

  "TRANSVERSAL": {
    "LIFECYCLE": { "$ref": "MetaSchema_IVCxDRO.TRANSVERSAL.LIFECYCLE" },
    "DRO_VECTOR": { "DEFINITION": [], "RULE": [], "OPTION": [] },
    "XMAP": { "by_path": {}, "aliases": {} }
  }
}


Comment lвҖҷagent вҖңconfronteвҖқ avec ce format (checks incontournables)


Double fractale


PrГ©sence de IDENTY/VIEW/CONTEXT, chacun avec DEFINITION/RULE/OPTION.


PrГ©sence de DRO_PROJECTION (miroir) pointant vers IVC (ou matГ©rialisГ©e).




Lifecycle


IDENTY.RULE.lifecycle_ref valide et TRANSVERSAL.LIFECYCLE existant.




Vecteur DRO


TRANSVERSAL.DRO_VECTOR prГ©sent (mГӘme vide), prГӘt Г  ГӘtre alimentГ© par lвҖҷagent (embeddings/poids/repГЁres).




Verbes вҶ’ mГ©thodes


Extraction des verbes dвҖҷaction dans le scГ©nario/brief.


Mapping vers mГ©thodes (get/create/update/validate/test/evaluate/optimize/render/linkвҖҰ).




Loops rГ©cursives


Parcours down (type вҶ’ Г©lГ©ments вҶ’ instances) Г  chaque step, avec retours successifs (get/create вҶ’ test/evaluate вҶ’ optimize вҶ’ render).





Ce quвҖҷil faut rГ©ellement crГ©er maintenant (version stricte & minimale)


schemas/MetaSchema_IVCxDRO.json (exactement comme ci-dessus).


3вҖ“5 schГ©mas cibles au mГӘme format (Website, Page, Company, Client, Asset).


catalogs/schemas_catalog.json (type вҶ’ chemin).


catalogs/methods_catalog.json (verbes вҶ’ mГ©thodes).


core/validators/double_fractal_check.py


VГ©rifie prГ©sence IVC.(D,R,O) + DRO_PROJECTION + TRANSVERSAL.LIFECYCLE + TRANSVERSAL.DRO_VECTOR.


Retourne missing[] (patch suggestions par chemin).




core/dro_vectorizer.py (stub)


Remplit TRANSVERSAL.DRO_VECTOR.{DEFINITION|RULE|OPTION} Г  partir du schГ©ma/objet.




core/extract_verbs_from_text.py (regex + liste)


runner/deploy_recursive.py


Loops (get/create вҶ’ test/evaluate вҶ’ optimize вҶ’ render), et confrontation au MetaSchema via double_fractal_check.




Tout le reste (prompts, Q&A, optimize loop) fonctionne tel que dГ©jГ  dГ©crit, mais sвҖҷappuie sur cette forme.
Si tu veux, je te fournis les squelettes fichier par fichier pour (1)вҶ’(8) au format exact ci-dessus.

Parfait вҖ” on sвҖҷaligne strictement sur ta forme, sans aucun autre niveau :
IDENTITY
DEFINITION
RULE
OPTION
VIEW
DEFINITION
RULE
OPTION
CONTEXT
DEFINITION
RULE
OPTION
Je te redonne le MetaSchema et un exemple Website en respectant exactement cette structure.
(Le lifecycle et le vecteur DRO sont intГ©grГ©s Г  lвҖҷintГ©rieur des blocs existants, pour ne pas ajouter de section au sommet.)
MetaSchema (IVCГ—DRO + lifecycle inclus, sans autre top-level)
jsonCopier le code{
  "IDENTITY": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "name": "<string>",
      "type": "<string>"
    },
    "RULE": {
      "required": ["id", "name", "type"],
      "validators": [],
      "lifecycle": {
        "state": "draft",
        "states": ["draft","defined","built","tested","optimized","rendered","archived"],
        "transitions": {
          "draft->defined": ["define","spec"],
          "defined->built": ["create","build","update"],
          "built->tested": ["test","validate","evaluate"],
          "tested->optimized": ["optimize","refactor","improve"],
          "optimized->rendered": ["render","publish","ship"],
          "rendered->archived": ["archive"]
        },
        "hooks": { "on_enter": {}, "on_exit": {} }
      }
    },
    "OPTION": {
      "timestamps": { "created_at": null, "updated_at": null, "state_changed_at": null },
      "dro_vector": { "definitions": [], "rules": [], "options": [] }
    }
  },

  "VIEW": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "status": "draft",
      "labels": []
    },
    "RULE": {
      "required": ["status"],
      "validators": []
    },
    "OPTION": {
      "ui": {},
      "formats": [],
      "dro_vector": { "definitions": [], "rules": [], "options": [] }
    }
  },

  "CONTEXT": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "relations": [],
      "tags": []
    },
    "RULE": {
      "required": [],
      "validators": []
    },
    "OPTION": {
      "scopes": [],
      "indices": [],
      "dro_vector": { "definitions": [], "rules": [], "options": [] }
    }
  }
}

Website.schema (conforme Г  la mГӘme forme)
jsonCopier le code{
  "IDENTITY": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "id": "<uuid>",
      "name": "<string>",
      "type": "Website"
    },
    "RULE": {
      "required": ["name", "type"],
      "validators": []
    },
    "OPTION": {}
  },

  "VIEW": {
    "DEFINITION": {
      "status": "draft",
      "labels": [],
      "domain": "<string>"
    },
    "RULE": {
      "required": ["status", "domain"],
      "validators": []
    },
